WEBVTT

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:06.836 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:06.836 --> 00:00:10.050 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.050 --> 00:00:13.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Meat production worldwide
is set to almost double by 2050

00:00:13.980 --> 00:00:18.720 align:middle line:84%
as nations become wealthier
and demand more animal protein.

00:00:18.720 --> 00:00:23.370 align:middle line:84%
>> To maintain our present level
of consumption at this present

00:00:23.370 --> 00:00:30.090 align:middle line:84%
time, beyond 2050, we would need
an additional half a planet.

00:00:30.090 --> 00:00:41.820 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:00:41.820 --> 00:00:44.310 align:middle line:84%
>> As I become a father
for the first time,

00:00:44.310 --> 00:00:46.830 align:middle line:84%
there are more and more
revelations about the way we

00:00:46.830 --> 00:00:51.310 align:middle line:84%
are raising the
animals that feed us.

00:00:51.310 --> 00:00:53.690 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:53.690 --> 00:00:58.460 align:middle line:90%


00:00:58.460 --> 00:01:01.550 align:middle line:84%
>> A major new study from the
World Health Organization has

00:01:01.550 --> 00:01:05.030 align:middle line:84%
revealed that eating processed
meat can cause cancer.

00:01:05.030 --> 00:01:19.440 align:middle line:90%


00:01:19.440 --> 00:01:22.440 align:middle line:84%
>> Meat consumption isn't just
the source of health problems.

00:01:22.440 --> 00:01:25.170 align:middle line:84%
It could also lead to
widespread species extinction

00:01:25.170 --> 00:01:29.320 align:middle line:84%
according to a recently
published study.

00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:32.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Feeding my son his
first mouthfuls and seeing

00:01:32.320 --> 00:01:35.740 align:middle line:84%
the animals around him through
his eyes has led me to look

00:01:35.740 --> 00:01:37.600 align:middle line:84%
at this information
in a new way.

00:01:37.600 --> 00:01:40.190 align:middle line:90%


00:01:40.190 --> 00:01:42.830 align:middle line:84%
It has caused me to
consider the choices that we

00:01:42.830 --> 00:01:46.640 align:middle line:84%
make to feed ourselves more
closely as if suddenly,

00:01:46.640 --> 00:01:49.700 align:middle line:84%
for him, I could no
longer remain indifferent

00:01:49.700 --> 00:01:50.960 align:middle line:90%
and had to find out more.

00:01:50.960 --> 00:01:54.530 align:middle line:90%


00:01:54.530 --> 00:01:57.650 align:middle line:84%
>> What's happened is
we've "rationalized"

00:01:57.650 --> 00:02:02.000 align:middle line:84%
and made efficient the
production of meat,

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:04.910 align:middle line:84%
and we've industrialized it
as we've industrialized almost

00:02:04.910 --> 00:02:07.640 align:middle line:84%
every other form of
production on earth.

00:02:07.640 --> 00:02:14.030 align:middle line:84%
And the efficiency allows us
to produce more meat than ever

00:02:14.030 --> 00:02:15.199 align:middle line:90%
before, by far.

00:02:15.199 --> 00:02:19.460 align:middle line:90%


00:02:19.460 --> 00:02:22.130 align:middle line:84%
Before World War
II, let's say, there

00:02:22.130 --> 00:02:24.800 align:middle line:84%
was none of what
we're talking about,

00:02:24.800 --> 00:02:28.940 align:middle line:84%
many people raising two pigs,
six pigs, 10 pigs, 20 pigs,

00:02:28.940 --> 00:02:30.200 align:middle line:90%
200 pigs.

00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:33.170 align:middle line:90%
No one was raising 10,000 pigs.

00:02:33.170 --> 00:02:35.940 align:middle line:90%
All pigs were pastured pigs.

00:02:35.940 --> 00:02:37.800 align:middle line:90%
Chickens, same kinds of thing.

00:02:37.800 --> 00:02:39.740 align:middle line:84%
They may have been
raised by the hundreds.

00:02:39.740 --> 00:02:42.720 align:middle line:84%
Now they're raised by the
hundreds of thousands.

00:02:42.720 --> 00:02:45.920 align:middle line:84%
So the scale has gone
from a human scale

00:02:45.920 --> 00:02:49.820 align:middle line:84%
that's comprehensible to a scale
that's really incomprehensible.

00:02:49.820 --> 00:02:53.450 align:middle line:84%
It's always "follow the money,"
and this is a profitable way

00:02:53.450 --> 00:02:54.530 align:middle line:90%
to do things.

00:02:54.530 --> 00:02:56.030 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to qualify
this statement,

00:02:56.030 --> 00:02:59.840 align:middle line:84%
but this is the cheapest way
to produce millions and even

00:02:59.840 --> 00:03:03.440 align:middle line:84%
billions of animals
for human consumption.

00:03:03.440 --> 00:03:06.230 align:middle line:84%
The problem is that the
system has an expiration date.

00:03:06.230 --> 00:03:09.180 align:middle line:90%


00:03:09.180 --> 00:03:12.390 align:middle line:84%
>> Is it still possible to feed
animals to our children while

00:03:12.390 --> 00:03:15.270 align:middle line:84%
respecting the planet,
the animals' welfare,

00:03:15.270 --> 00:03:16.890 align:middle line:90%
and our health?

00:03:16.890 --> 00:03:19.380 align:middle line:84%
I'm not an animal
rights activist.

00:03:19.380 --> 00:03:20.643 align:middle line:90%
I'm a journalist.

00:03:20.643 --> 00:03:26.440 align:middle line:90%


00:03:26.440 --> 00:03:28.470 align:middle line:84%
The best way to
answer this question

00:03:28.470 --> 00:03:30.660 align:middle line:90%
is to go out into the field.

00:03:30.660 --> 00:03:32.550 align:middle line:84%
Traveling all over
the world, I'm

00:03:32.550 --> 00:03:34.500 align:middle line:84%
going to meet with
men and women who

00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:37.590 align:middle line:84%
are inventing innovative
ways of raising animals

00:03:37.590 --> 00:03:40.305 align:middle line:84%
that respect man,
nature, and animals.

00:03:40.305 --> 00:03:44.370 align:middle line:90%


00:03:44.370 --> 00:03:46.320 align:middle line:84%
I want to put these
initiatives together

00:03:46.320 --> 00:03:48.450 align:middle line:84%
to find out if another
way of consumption

00:03:48.450 --> 00:03:51.930 align:middle line:84%
is possible and viable
and if there is still time

00:03:51.930 --> 00:03:54.040 align:middle line:90%
left to do things differently.

00:03:54.040 --> 00:03:58.890 align:middle line:84%
>> We created-- we created
industrial agriculture.

00:03:58.890 --> 00:04:00.510 align:middle line:90%
It was intentional.

00:04:00.510 --> 00:04:03.720 align:middle line:84%
There was a decision made
to say, how can we produce

00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:05.800 align:middle line:90%
the most grain possible?

00:04:05.800 --> 00:04:09.070 align:middle line:84%
How can we produce the
most animals possible?

00:04:09.070 --> 00:04:11.250 align:middle line:84%
There were other directions
we could have gone in.

00:04:11.250 --> 00:04:14.130 align:middle line:84%
We could have said, how can
we make the healthiest diet

00:04:14.130 --> 00:04:16.000 align:middle line:90%
for our people possible?

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:19.260 align:middle line:84%
How can we make sure that our
land is poisoned as little as

00:04:19.260 --> 00:04:20.320 align:middle line:90%
possible?

00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:24.000 align:middle line:84%
How can we exhibit
humaneness towards animals

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:25.260 align:middle line:90%
as much as possible?

00:04:25.260 --> 00:04:29.100 align:middle line:84%
We chose to ignore those
issues in favor of yield.

00:04:29.100 --> 00:04:31.527 align:middle line:84%
Now it's time to move in
a different direction.

00:04:31.527 --> 00:04:56.390 align:middle line:90%


00:04:56.390 --> 00:04:59.830 align:middle line:84%
>> I heard about a man in the
plains of the American Midwest

00:04:59.830 --> 00:05:02.920 align:middle line:84%
who decided to challenge the
dominant industrial model.

00:05:02.920 --> 00:05:06.610 align:middle line:90%


00:05:06.610 --> 00:05:09.220 align:middle line:84%
He has developed a new
method of livestock farming

00:05:09.220 --> 00:05:12.400 align:middle line:84%
that is closer to nature
to prove that doing things

00:05:12.400 --> 00:05:13.950 align:middle line:90%
differently is still possible.

00:05:13.950 --> 00:05:18.120 align:middle line:90%


00:05:18.120 --> 00:05:24.090 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm Jude Becker, and my farm
has been operated by me since I

00:05:24.090 --> 00:05:28.170 align:middle line:84%
returned from the
University in 1999.

00:05:28.170 --> 00:05:31.470 align:middle line:84%
And the farm is
certified organic.

00:05:31.470 --> 00:05:34.560 align:middle line:84%
I began this system
with only six sows,

00:05:34.560 --> 00:05:37.470 align:middle line:90%
and today we have 150.

00:05:37.470 --> 00:05:44.430 align:middle line:84%
And we are producing more
than 2,000 pigs per year.

00:05:44.430 --> 00:05:47.910 align:middle line:84%
My farm could be considered
the opposite system

00:05:47.910 --> 00:05:53.400 align:middle line:90%
from the industrial philosophy.

00:05:53.400 --> 00:05:58.020 align:middle line:84%
Our philosophy is based on
allowing the pigs to express

00:05:58.020 --> 00:06:02.040 align:middle line:84%
their natural instincts because
this promotes animal welfare,

00:06:02.040 --> 00:06:03.960 align:middle line:84%
and I think it promotes
health of the animals.

00:06:03.960 --> 00:06:12.010 align:middle line:90%


00:06:12.010 --> 00:06:15.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Jude Becker's system is
set up so that pigs live

00:06:15.220 --> 00:06:19.180 align:middle line:84%
in the open air all year around,
whatever the temperature.

00:06:19.180 --> 00:06:22.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Here is something
we call a mud wallow.

00:06:22.900 --> 00:06:26.980 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the natural
instincts for a sow to remain

00:06:26.980 --> 00:06:29.430 align:middle line:90%
cool because she cannot sweat.

00:06:29.430 --> 00:06:33.510 align:middle line:84%
And so in summertime, if
the weather is very hot,

00:06:33.510 --> 00:06:37.000 align:middle line:84%
it's so important for
the sow to come here

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:41.170 align:middle line:84%
occasionally during the
most hot time in the day.

00:06:41.170 --> 00:06:44.490 align:middle line:90%


00:06:44.490 --> 00:06:46.530 align:middle line:84%
If we are very quiet,
I will show you

00:06:46.530 --> 00:06:49.710 align:middle line:84%
a litter of piglets which
was born during the night.

00:06:49.710 --> 00:06:55.170 align:middle line:90%


00:06:55.170 --> 00:06:57.420 align:middle line:84%
You can see there
are about 12 pigs.

00:06:57.420 --> 00:07:00.850 align:middle line:90%


00:07:00.850 --> 00:07:05.060 align:middle line:90%
Well, this house is insulated.

00:07:05.060 --> 00:07:11.090 align:middle line:84%
And there is around 10
centimeters of insulation,

00:07:11.090 --> 00:07:13.280 align:middle line:90%
so the wall is quite thick.

00:07:13.280 --> 00:07:16.060 align:middle line:84%
And it's made of steel,
so it's very strong.

00:07:16.060 --> 00:07:19.310 align:middle line:84%
And in winter, it keeps
the sow quite warm.

00:07:19.310 --> 00:07:22.250 align:middle line:84%
And also it keeps the
heat out in summer

00:07:22.250 --> 00:07:29.040 align:middle line:84%
because we open the back
window and keep ventilation.

00:07:29.040 --> 00:07:31.860 align:middle line:90%
It's a more natural system.

00:07:31.860 --> 00:07:36.210 align:middle line:84%
The pig can grow
in its natural way

00:07:36.210 --> 00:07:40.590 align:middle line:84%
by living outside and
experiencing the earth.

00:07:40.590 --> 00:07:45.960 align:middle line:84%
Because a pig has this special
nose to dig in the earth,

00:07:45.960 --> 00:07:51.030 align:middle line:84%
and if it cannot have this,
then it's not complete.

00:07:51.030 --> 00:07:52.890 align:middle line:90%
It's not completely a pig.

00:07:52.890 --> 00:07:53.790 align:middle line:90%
Something is missing.

00:07:53.790 --> 00:07:57.440 align:middle line:90%


00:07:57.440 --> 00:08:00.230 align:middle line:84%
>> This kind of farming
resembles the images that we

00:08:00.230 --> 00:08:01.730 align:middle line:90%
see in adverts.

00:08:01.730 --> 00:08:04.850 align:middle line:84%
However, over 80%
of pig meat doesn't

00:08:04.850 --> 00:08:07.250 align:middle line:84%
come from farms
like Jude Becker's

00:08:07.250 --> 00:08:09.400 align:middle line:84%
but from industrial
farms like this one.

00:08:09.400 --> 00:08:16.680 align:middle line:90%


00:08:16.680 --> 00:08:21.840 align:middle line:84%
Here, everything happens
inside the buildings.

00:08:21.840 --> 00:08:23.590 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:08:23.590 --> 00:09:27.920 align:middle line:90%


00:09:27.920 --> 00:09:29.700 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:09:29.700 --> 00:09:54.390 align:middle line:90%


00:09:54.390 --> 00:09:58.380 align:middle line:84%
>> 95% percent of pork produced
in France comes from farms like

00:09:58.380 --> 00:09:59.180 align:middle line:90%
this one.

00:09:59.180 --> 00:10:03.530 align:middle line:90%


00:10:03.530 --> 00:10:04.720 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:10:04.720 --> 00:10:05.678 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:10:05.678 --> 00:10:10.050 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:10:10.050 --> 00:10:12.210 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:10:12.210 --> 00:10:46.380 align:middle line:90%


00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:48.585 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:10:48.585 --> 00:10:53.880 align:middle line:90%


00:10:53.880 --> 00:10:56.860 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:10:56.860 --> 00:11:15.760 align:middle line:90%


00:11:15.760 --> 00:11:18.610 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:11:18.610 --> 00:11:42.580 align:middle line:90%


00:11:42.580 --> 00:11:45.290 align:middle line:84%
>> So here you don't
use gestation cages?

00:11:45.290 --> 00:11:49.170 align:middle line:84%
>> No, we don't need any
kind of a crate or cage.

00:11:49.170 --> 00:11:53.370 align:middle line:84%
It's not necessary
in this system.

00:11:53.370 --> 00:11:55.770 align:middle line:84%
In the outdoor
system, we are relying

00:11:55.770 --> 00:11:59.790 align:middle line:84%
on the instincts, the
motherly instincts of the sow

00:11:59.790 --> 00:12:01.950 align:middle line:90%
to raise her piglets.

00:12:01.950 --> 00:12:05.970 align:middle line:84%
And so we don't spend too
many hours here every day.

00:12:05.970 --> 00:12:08.560 align:middle line:90%


00:12:08.560 --> 00:12:09.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Come on.

00:12:09.360 --> 00:12:10.193 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow, there's one.

00:12:10.193 --> 00:12:11.180 align:middle line:90%
You can see one is--

00:12:11.180 --> 00:12:13.825 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah.

00:12:13.825 --> 00:12:15.180 align:middle line:90%
Do you know why?

00:12:15.180 --> 00:12:17.640 align:middle line:84%
>> It looks like she just
laid down on top of that pig.

00:12:17.640 --> 00:12:21.730 align:middle line:90%


00:12:21.730 --> 00:12:24.490 align:middle line:84%
Practitioners of the
indoor industrial system

00:12:24.490 --> 00:12:28.120 align:middle line:84%
say that we have
more piglets which

00:12:28.120 --> 00:12:31.240 align:middle line:84%
are crushed by their
mother, so this

00:12:31.240 --> 00:12:32.590 align:middle line:90%
is something we got recently.

00:12:32.590 --> 00:12:35.290 align:middle line:90%
That house is bigger.

00:12:35.290 --> 00:12:37.420 align:middle line:84%
It looks the same
as the other house,

00:12:37.420 --> 00:12:42.100 align:middle line:84%
but the one difference is,
this house is a bit larger.

00:12:42.100 --> 00:12:44.740 align:middle line:84%
And just to make the
house a bit larger

00:12:44.740 --> 00:12:48.490 align:middle line:84%
could be the solution to
the problem of crushing.

00:12:48.490 --> 00:12:51.325 align:middle line:84%
And if that's true, it
could be a big success.

00:12:51.325 --> 00:12:55.960 align:middle line:90%


00:12:55.960 --> 00:12:59.380 align:middle line:84%
>> This natural farming
method proves that solving one

00:12:59.380 --> 00:13:02.350 align:middle line:84%
of the other great scandals
of industrial farming,

00:13:02.350 --> 00:13:06.640 align:middle line:84%
the extensive use of
antibiotics, is also possible.

00:13:06.640 --> 00:13:09.400 align:middle line:84%
>> Because of the crowding
that these animals experience

00:13:09.400 --> 00:13:12.990 align:middle line:84%
because of the ways
that they're raised,

00:13:12.990 --> 00:13:15.070 align:middle line:90%
disease is a big problem.

00:13:15.070 --> 00:13:19.450 align:middle line:84%
So it developed that
antibiotics began

00:13:19.450 --> 00:13:22.870 align:middle line:84%
to be given to animals
routinely, prophylactically,

00:13:22.870 --> 00:13:24.400 align:middle line:90%
to prevent disease.

00:13:24.400 --> 00:13:27.040 align:middle line:84%
And also, incidentally,
there was some evidence,

00:13:27.040 --> 00:13:30.370 align:middle line:84%
there is some evidence,
that by giving antibiotics

00:13:30.370 --> 00:13:32.140 align:middle line:84%
to young animals,
you're making them

00:13:32.140 --> 00:13:35.050 align:middle line:84%
grow more quickly and
bigger because healthier

00:13:35.050 --> 00:13:38.860 align:middle line:84%
animals grow more
quickly and bigger.

00:13:38.860 --> 00:13:41.290 align:middle line:90%
So what's the problem with this?

00:13:41.290 --> 00:13:44.060 align:middle line:84%
Because bacteria are
smart, able to adapt,

00:13:44.060 --> 00:13:47.380 align:middle line:84%
they're breeding resistance
to these antibiotics.

00:13:47.380 --> 00:13:50.350 align:middle line:84%
As they do that in
the animal population,

00:13:50.350 --> 00:13:52.930 align:middle line:84%
they transfer that
resistance to bacteria that

00:13:52.930 --> 00:13:55.000 align:middle line:90%
affect the human population.

00:13:55.000 --> 00:14:00.430 align:middle line:84%
And as a result of that, we
are seeing increased number

00:14:00.430 --> 00:14:03.280 align:middle line:84%
of infections,
people in hospitals

00:14:03.280 --> 00:14:08.710 align:middle line:84%
and out of hospitals for
whom antibiotics don't work.

00:14:08.710 --> 00:14:12.340 align:middle line:84%
The number of people who die
from antibiotic-resistant

00:14:12.340 --> 00:14:16.060 align:middle line:84%
bacterial infections in the
United States is about 25,000

00:14:16.060 --> 00:14:17.980 align:middle line:90%
a year and rising.

00:14:17.980 --> 00:14:20.200 align:middle line:84%
The number of people
who get sick and have

00:14:20.200 --> 00:14:23.260 align:middle line:84%
trouble getting better is in
the hundreds of thousands.

00:14:23.260 --> 00:14:25.390 align:middle line:84%
That's an issue that's
not going to go away.

00:14:25.390 --> 00:14:28.320 align:middle line:90%


00:14:28.320 --> 00:14:32.910 align:middle line:84%
>> In France, antibiotic
resistance kills 13,000 people

00:14:32.910 --> 00:14:33.870 align:middle line:90%
a year.

00:14:33.870 --> 00:14:38.310 align:middle line:84%
According to a British study, if
nothing changes, in 2050, this

00:14:38.310 --> 00:14:41.080 align:middle line:84%
could be the number one
cause of death in the world,

00:14:41.080 --> 00:14:43.530 align:middle line:84%
causing 10 million
deaths each year.

00:14:43.530 --> 00:14:50.200 align:middle line:90%


00:14:50.200 --> 00:14:54.040 align:middle line:84%
>> On my farm, we are not
allowed to use antibiotics.

00:14:54.040 --> 00:14:57.010 align:middle line:84%
And I believe this
is the right decision

00:14:57.010 --> 00:15:00.160 align:middle line:90%
for organic farms in the US.

00:15:00.160 --> 00:15:01.990 align:middle line:84%
It's one point of
differentiation

00:15:01.990 --> 00:15:04.190 align:middle line:84%
between the European
Union and the US

00:15:04.190 --> 00:15:09.880 align:middle line:84%
is we're not allowed to use
them unless the animal requires

00:15:09.880 --> 00:15:14.400 align:middle line:84%
medicine to prevent
death or suffering.

00:15:14.400 --> 00:15:18.200 align:middle line:84%
And if we use that antibiotic,
we need to separate,

00:15:18.200 --> 00:15:21.940 align:middle line:84%
we need to segregate that
treated animal from the rest

00:15:21.940 --> 00:15:25.240 align:middle line:84%
and sell it to the
conventional system.

00:15:25.240 --> 00:15:28.610 align:middle line:90%


00:15:28.610 --> 00:15:31.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Jude's meat costs three times
more than industrially farmed

00:15:31.700 --> 00:15:32.500 align:middle line:90%
meat.

