00:35:03.120 --> 00:35:05.550 align:middle line:90%
and preserves biodiversity.

00:35:05.550 --> 00:36:39.050 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:36:39.050 --> 00:36:42.000 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:43.750 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:36:43.750 --> 00:37:57.850 align:middle line:90%


00:37:57.850 --> 00:38:01.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Over the last 20 years, our
consumption of fish has more

00:38:01.420 --> 00:38:02.960 align:middle line:90%
than doubled.

00:38:02.960 --> 00:38:05.200 align:middle line:84%
Anne Marie's fishing
method might not

00:38:05.200 --> 00:38:08.080 align:middle line:84%
be able to feed the
planet, but at our level,

00:38:08.080 --> 00:38:11.270 align:middle line:84%
opting for fish from
sustainable fishing like hers,

00:38:11.270 --> 00:38:13.300 align:middle line:84%
even if they are a
bit more expensive,

00:38:13.300 --> 00:38:16.400 align:middle line:84%
is the first step in
the right direction.

00:38:16.400 --> 00:38:18.010 align:middle line:90%
They may not be perfect yet.

00:38:18.010 --> 00:38:21.190 align:middle line:84%
But whether it's on a small
scale or a large scale,

00:38:21.190 --> 00:38:23.725 align:middle line:84%
methods that respect
animals already exist.

00:38:23.725 --> 00:38:36.200 align:middle line:90%


00:38:36.200 --> 00:38:38.740 align:middle line:84%
But respecting animals
is not the only thing

00:38:38.740 --> 00:38:42.130 align:middle line:84%
we should take into account
